who   : The Captain — The Captain (the title that became a name).
what  : Known by no other name. The original commander of the Black Company; the title that became a name. He held them together through the hardest years and, when he fell, passed the title to Croaker. The Annals record his death — the exact circumstance is theirs to tell, not mine to invent.
